### Portfolio Backend API Test File
### Use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar HTTP client tools
### Or use the curl commands below in your terminal

### Variables (Update these based on your Laravel server)
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api

### Test 1: POST /api/contact - Valid Request
POST {{apiUrl}}/contact
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890",
  "message": "This is a test message from the API test file. Please ignore."
}

### Test 2: POST /api/contact - Without Phone (Optional Field)
POST {{apiUrl}}/contact
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "message": "Testing contact form without phone number."
}

### Test 3: POST /api/contact - Validation Error (Missing Required Fields)
POST {{apiUrl}}/contact
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "message": ""
}

### Test 4: POST /api/contact - Rate Limit Test (Run this 6 times quickly)
POST {{apiUrl}}/contact
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Rate Limit Test",
  "email": "ratelimit@example.com",
  "message": "Testing rate limiting - should fail on 6th request."
}

